external_knowledge:
- 'Shining stars' refers to the top 3 ranked and top 3 points-awarded athletes;
- 'Junior athletes' refers to athletes in the 'Junior' category;
- 'Regional competitions' refers to competitions at the regional level;
- 'Guiding mentors' refers to the most recent coaches of the athletes;
- 'Paths to glory' refers to the athletes' achievements in the sport.

- "older athletes" refers to athletes who are older than 25 years;
- "heavily attended competitions" refers to competitions with more than 50 participants;
- "excelled" means achieving a score higher than 80.

- "Top-ranked athletes" refers to athletes who are ranked first in their respective categories;
- "Training sessions more effective than their average" implies that the effectiveness score of a specific training session is higher than the average effectiveness score of all sessions for that athlete;
- "Senior National category" is a classification for athletes competing at the national level in the senior age group.

- 'Senior' category refers to athletes who are typically older and more experienced.;
- 'International' level indicates competitions that are held at a global scale.;
- 'Top 10 ranked' means the athletes are among the best 10 in their respective year based on their performance points.;
- The coaching relationship start date is used to filter out relationships that began after January 1, 2020.

- 'Shining stars' refers to athletes with high points in the rankings (points >= 100);
- 'Coaches who light up the training sessions with their expertise' refers to coaches with an average session effectiveness greater than 7.5;
- 'Exceled in the top three positions' means athletes who have finished in the top 3 positions in at least one competition;
- 'Currently mentored' means the athlete-coach relationship has not ended (`end_date IS NULL`).

- "shining stars" refers to the top-ranked athletes;
- "maintained the top spot" means they have the lowest average rank, which corresponds to rank 1;
- "since 2020" means the rankings are considered from the year 2020 onwards.

- "shining stars" refers to athletes ranked in the top 10 for a specific sport;
- "guiding mentors" refers to coaches;
- "moment they embarked on their journey together" refers to the start date of the athlete-coach relationship;
- "chosen arena" refers to the sport with sport_id = 1;
- "crowned with a medal" indicates that the athlete has won a medal.

- 'Senior' category refers to a specific age group in the competition;
- 'Sport with ID 1' is a placeholder for a specific sport, such as track and field or swimming;
- 'Outperformed their own average score' means the athlete's score in a particular competition is higher than their average score across all gold medal-winning competitions in the 'Senior' category.

- The total points for each coach are calculated by summing the points of all athletes they have coached.;
- The coach with the highest total points is considered the top coach.;
- The points are from the rankings of the athletes in different years.

- "Top-ranked athletes" refers to those who were ranked 1st in 2022;
- "Highly effective coaches" are those with an average session effectiveness score greater than 8;
- "Consistently coached" means the coaching relationship started before 2022 and either has not ended or ended after 2022.

- 'Seasoned jumpers' refers to athletes who have participated in more than one competition in the 'Long Jump' event;
- 'Soared more than once' means the athlete has competed in the 'Long Jump' event in more than one competition;
- 'Sum of their leaping prowess' refers to the total score achieved by the athlete in the 'Long Jump' event.
